The Situation Room
Live from Washington
Monday, April 30, 2007

IN THE NEWS:
•	Suicide Bomber Strikes Shiite Funeral; at Least 22 Dead
•	5 Pennsylvania Campuses Remain Closed After E-mail Threat
•	More Money, More Money: Millionaire Households at a Record

IN POLITICS:
•	Wolfowitz Blasts “Smear Campaign,” Vows to Stay on at World Bank
•	New Jersey Governor Corzine Leaves Hospital

IN THE CAFFERTY FILE:
•	Should the Iraqi parliament take a two-month summer vacation?
•	Some former CIA officers want George Tenet to return the Medal of Freedom and to give book royalties to soldiers wounded in Iraq. Are they right?
•	What does it mean if terror attacks worldwide were up 30% last year?

